                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/324: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-15T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 15, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 15—7:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>949. I am informed that it is probable that League Secretariat or League
                    Commission will ask <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_MMGFR1">General
                        McCoy</persName> to remain at Geneva for the purpose of assisting in
                    discussion of Sino-Japanese questions when Commission returns to Europe.
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_MMGFR1">McCoy</persName> in a personal and
                    confidential conversation, which I had with him the other day (and before above
                    information came to me) intimated that he felt somewhat diffident about being
                    present in Geneva and would go directly home. I was disposed to agree with him
                    that from the American point of view his presence there might not be convenient.
                    However, having now had this intimation and without his knowledge I am
                    communicating this to you in order that, if desired, [you may have?] an
                    opportunity to consider the matter and transmit such views as you care to
                    transmit on the subject.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
